&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    INIT PHASE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;**************************************************
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Distribution &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; of the machine is amzn.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Distribution of the machine is Amazon Linux.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Revision of the distribution is 2.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;bastin is using IAM authentication with AWS region ap-northeast-1.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;There is no existing version of the AWS Discovery Agent on the machine.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Using rpm and yum &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; package management. Expected agent package name is aws-discovery-agent.rpm.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Installing using &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;local&lt;/span&gt; file /home/ec2-user/ads/aws-discovery-agent.rpm
